	<div class="wpb_text_column wpb_content_element " >
		<div class="wpb_wrapper">
			<p>This product has been developed to cater to all budgets offering the shooter a high quality product at an affordable price, with the performance and reliability equal to that of our more higher spec products.</p>

		</div>
	</div>
</div></div><div class="vc_tta-panel features" id="features" data-vc-content=".vc_tta-panel-body"><div class="vc_tta-panel-heading"><h4 class="vc_tta-panel-title"><a href="#features" data-vc-accordion data-vc-container=".vc_tta-container"><span class="vc_tta-title-text">Features</span></a></h4></div><div class="vc_tta-panel-body">
	<div class="wpb_text_column wpb_content_element " >
		<div class="wpb_wrapper">
			<ol>
<li>This model has been developed for the recreational or commercial shooter where high output and or exposure to harsh environments are a daily occurrence.</li>
<li>The 22 WM ST model will fit on even the shortest barrel lengths with only a minimum of 0.59″ (15mm) barrel required.</li>
<li>Can be retro-fitted onto multiple calibre rifles from .17 MACH II, .22 long-rifle, 17 HMR through to 22 Winchester Magnum.</li>
<li>This model is constructed using only quality corrosion resistance materials, with high resistance to flame degradation, retaining structual integrity.</li>
<li>No internal cleaning or maintenance required.</li>
<li>10,000x round minimum service life.</li>
<li>Fully sealed and welded construction for maximum service life.</li>
<li>High corrosion resistance to salt water exposure.</li>
<li>Improved recoil reduction for solid target aquisition.</li>
<li><strong>Warranty: </strong>3 years</li>
</ol>

		</div>
	</div>
</div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
